{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Te7AJNS9Jtz7DteYahPK2F","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cats are small, agile predators that have lived alongside humans for thousands of years, originally domesticated to control rodents in early agricultural societies. They are famously independent compared to dogs, yet they form strong bonds with their owners and often communicate affection through slow blinks, purring, and head-butts. A cat's body is built for hunting: flexible spines, retractable claws, sharp night vision, and whiskers sensitive enough to gauge whether a gap is wide enough to squeeze through. They sleep an astonishing 12–16 hours a day, conserving energy for short, explosive bursts of activity that mimic stalking prey. Despite their reputation for aloofness, cats are deeply curious, playful, and emotionally attuned creatures that bring warmth and quiet companionship into a home."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5635,"cache_read_input_tokens":3057,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5635},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cea94a3f-592d-4b53-9c51-461b732f5678","uuid":"43ed2f03-f4c8-4f6b-927a-d552d0894667"}
